File: The 29-year-old man allegedly took the two-year-old from a trolley while his grandmother was distracted, making a purchase. UMHLANGA - A man was arrested after attempting to abduct a child from a shopping centre on Thursday in Umhlanga. The 29-year-old man allegedly took the two-year-old from a trolley while his grandmother was distracted, making a purchase. The man was reportedly dressed in a security guard's uniform. WATCH: Kidnappings on the rise in South Africa Once the grandmother noticed the child was gone, she ran in search of the boy and recovered him from the man. The man was arrested and a case of kidnapping was opened at the North Durban police station.